{"word":"ἀναιδής","slug":"ἀναιδής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναιδής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αἰδώς'><el>αἰδώς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>shameless</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἀναιδέα δηϊοτῆτος</el> <i>insatiate</i> of strife, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <el>λᾶας ἀναιδής</el> <i>the reckless</i> stone, of Sisyphus, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>ἔργ' ἀναιδῆ</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: —<el>τὸ ἀναιδές</el>, <a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> <el>τἀνειδές,  ἀναίδεια</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἐπὶ τὸ ἀναιδέστερον τραπέσθαι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-δῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}